Embu Senator Lenny Kivuti has promised residents he won t abandon them if they elect him governor.He spoke on Sunday at the Full Gospel Church in Kiritiri Market when Retired Senior Bishop Samuel Muriithi asked him whether he will serve residents selflessly.Kivuti said those are virtues he practices. He said he will improve the existing cohesion, look fully into the welfare of residents so they can have good livelihoods.Kivuti said he will not divide Embu residents along clan or tribal lines and as a leader he will consult stakeholders in every sector to come up with the best solution.